  "description": "Where Connect's bytes live: the four storage layers, native 2x duplication (PGlite+Postgres), 3x when Switchboard+Swarm run together.",
  "orientation": "Running Connect over multiple transports has a real storage cost. This MOC consolidates the duplication analysis: operations live in up to four layers (PGlite, Postgres via Switchboard, Swarm /bytes, per-user op feeds), each with distinct durability and read characteristics. The native dual-store already puts every op in PGlite and Postgres; adding Swarm mirrors the same pattern at the remote layer, raising total cost to 3x. Collaboration adds SyncEnvelope wrappers and per-user feeds but does not re-duplicate raw ops. A typical small user totals ~120 KB \u2014 the order-of-magnitude baseline for capacity discussions.",
